  "poem": {
    "content": "In a pudding-colored room, shadows flee,\nA woman sits, stirring coffee, dark as sea.\nTwo lizards scuttle, a tag of yesterday's play,\nWhile outside, dramas unfold, day by day.\n\nLive wires hum, an antenna reaching high,\nTo catch whispers of secrets drifting by.\nAn angry echo in the cotton-stuffed chair,\nAs moonlight paints the room with pale despair.\n\nShe tries to conduct herself with careful grace,\nBut memories claw at her time-worn face.\nA yearning lingers, a soft and tender plea,\nTo enhance the moments that used to be.\n\nThe coffee cools, a bitter, acrid taste,\nIn this quiet room, her heart held in waste.\nShe wishes only to flee this desolate scene,\nWhere shadows dance, and dreams grow lean.",
